WEBVTT



00:00:00.270 --> 00:00:05.610
Welcome my friend to today's
lecture on roles of RBI ever felt

00:00:05.610 --> 00:00:07.740
like your brain needed a power up.

00:00:07.980 --> 00:00:09.030
This is it.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:15.210
The Reserve Bank of India or RBI is
the big boss of all banks in India.

00:00:15.660 --> 00:00:22.320
It kicked off its operations on April
1st, 1935 under the RBI Act of 1934.

00:00:23.075 --> 00:00:27.335
Its main job, its derma, is to
manage our country's monetary

00:00:27.335 --> 00:00:29.255
policy and financial system.

00:00:29.705 --> 00:00:34.685
Think of RBI as the banker's bank and
the government's bank, playing the

00:00:34.685 --> 00:00:39.635
crucial role of a captain to steer the
economy towards stability and growth.

00:00:40.085 --> 00:00:44.315
It's the one managing our currency,
wrestling with inflation, keeping

00:00:44.315 --> 00:00:45.905
an eye on commercial banks.

00:00:46.065 --> 00:00:47.985
And handling our foreign exchange.

00:00:48.345 --> 00:00:53.355
So let's get into its key
roles, concept explanation.

00:00:53.775 --> 00:00:57.165
First up, the RBI is a monetary authority.

00:00:57.555 --> 00:01:02.355
This means it formulates, implements,
and monitors the monetary policy.

00:01:02.709 --> 00:01:03.819
What's the main goal?

00:01:04.030 --> 00:01:05.619
To keep prices stable?

00:01:05.830 --> 00:01:06.520
AKA.

00:01:06.670 --> 00:01:10.509
Keep inflation in check while
also supporting economic growth.

00:01:10.990 --> 00:01:15.699
It has a toolkit for this with fancy
names like repo rate, reverse repo

00:01:15.699 --> 00:01:21.970
rate, cash reserve ratio, or CRR and
statutory liquidity ratio or SLR,

00:01:22.235 --> 00:01:24.039
all to control the money supply.

00:01:24.735 --> 00:01:29.085
Next, it's the regulator and
supervisor of the financial system.

00:01:29.475 --> 00:01:32.745
The RBI sets the playground
rules for all banks.

00:01:33.105 --> 00:01:37.575
Its aim is to maintain our trust in the
banking system, protect the money of

00:01:37.575 --> 00:01:42.980
depositors like you and me, and ensure we
get good cost-effective banking services.

00:01:43.865 --> 00:01:47.105
This involves everything from
giving out licenses to new

00:01:47.105 --> 00:01:51.365
banks, to conducting surprise
inspections and setting guidelines.

00:01:51.935 --> 00:01:57.305
It is also the manager of Foreign
Exchange RBI manages the Foreign Exchange

00:01:57.305 --> 00:02:00.366
Management Act, or FEMA from 1999.

00:02:01.130 --> 00:02:05.839
This is to make foreign trade and payments
smooth and to ensure the foreign exchange

00:02:05.839 --> 00:02:08.269
market in India grows in an orderly way.

00:02:08.750 --> 00:02:13.370
You'll often see it jump into the market
to make sure our rupees value doesn't

00:02:13.370 --> 00:02:15.440
go on a crazy rollercoaster ride.

00:02:16.040 --> 00:02:20.660
Another very visible role is
as the issuer of currency, that

00:02:20.690 --> 00:02:22.490
crisp new note in your wallet.

00:02:22.640 --> 00:02:23.900
That's from the RBI.

00:02:24.555 --> 00:02:28.305
It issues and exchanges, currency
notes and coins, making sure

00:02:28.305 --> 00:02:29.775
there's enough cash flowing.

00:02:30.135 --> 00:02:35.415
It also has the job of taking back old
one-out currency that is no longer fit

00:02:35.415 --> 00:02:39.375
for circulation, which helps maintain
public confidence in our money.

00:02:40.109 --> 00:02:42.329
Then there's its developmental role.

00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:45.179
RBI isn't just a strict regulator.

00:02:45.420 --> 00:02:47.190
It also has a soft side.

00:02:47.549 --> 00:02:51.299
It performs many promotional
functions to support national goals.

00:02:51.720 --> 00:02:55.739
This includes pushing for financial
inclusion so that even people in

00:02:55.739 --> 00:02:57.750
remote villages get banking services.

00:02:58.330 --> 00:03:01.930
Developing specialized financial
institutions and supporting

00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:05.800
crucial sectors like agriculture
and small scale industries.

00:03:06.400 --> 00:03:09.370
The RBI is also the banker to government.

00:03:09.730 --> 00:03:13.870
It acts like a merchant banker for
both the central and state governments.

00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:17.590
It handles their accounts, receives
money, and makes payments for

00:03:17.595 --> 00:03:19.480
them, and manages public debt.

00:03:19.960 --> 00:03:24.250
It's also the wise advisor the government
turns to for financial matters.

00:03:24.600 --> 00:03:27.420
And finally, it is the banker to banks.

00:03:27.810 --> 00:03:30.990
Just like you have an account
with a bank, all commercial

00:03:30.990 --> 00:03:32.670
banks have accounts with the RBI.

00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:37.860
It gives them short-term loans through
the repo window, and most importantly,

00:03:37.980 --> 00:03:40.230
acts as a lender of last resort.

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:43.980
It also helps banks settle
transactions with each other.

00:03:44.785 --> 00:03:46.255
Real world relevance.

00:03:46.645 --> 00:03:52.045
Now, understanding these rules is super
important because RBI's actions directly

00:03:52.045 --> 00:03:56.725
hit banking operations, interest rates,
and all the rules banks must follow.

00:03:57.115 --> 00:04:00.175
It helps you understand the
whole economic picture that

00:04:00.175 --> 00:04:02.394
influences every banking decision.

00:04:02.730 --> 00:04:07.500
For instance, RBI's policies directly
impact day-to-day banking operations,

00:04:07.650 --> 00:04:11.700
like how much cash a bank must keep
in reserve, and how much it can lend.

00:04:12.150 --> 00:04:15.930
The interest rates on your loans
and deposits are heavily influenced

00:04:15.930 --> 00:04:21.030
by changes in RBI's, key rates like
repo and reverse repo for banks.

00:04:21.149 --> 00:04:26.310
Understanding RBI's regulatory compliance
framework is non-negotiable to avoid

00:04:26.310 --> 00:04:28.050
penalties and protect customers.

00:04:28.770 --> 00:04:33.300
And on a macro level, RBI's
decisions shape the entire economic

00:04:33.300 --> 00:04:37.710
environment affecting inflation,
currency stability, and the financial

