00:07:20.420 --> 00:07:22.550
A very common mistake is confusing.

00:07:22.550 --> 00:07:24.320
RBI with commercial banks.

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:26.300
RBI is the central bank.

00:07:26.420 --> 00:07:28.130
It doesn't deal with us directly.

00:07:28.490 --> 00:07:32.300
Another classic blunder is mixing
up monetary and fiscal policy.

00:07:32.630 --> 00:07:34.430
Monetary policy is RBI's.

00:07:34.430 --> 00:07:38.000
Job fiscal policy involving
taxes and government spending

00:07:38.090 --> 00:07:39.380
belongs to the government.

00:07:39.770 --> 00:07:42.860
Also, don't assume RBI
regulates everything.

00:07:43.070 --> 00:07:46.760
SEBI handles capital markets
and IRDA handles insurance.

00:07:47.180 --> 00:07:48.050
Misunderstanding.

00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:50.780
The term lender of last
resort is also common.

00:07:51.020 --> 00:07:54.680
It's to help solvent banks with
temporary cash shortages, not to

00:07:54.680 --> 00:07:56.390
blindly bail out failing ones.

00:07:56.690 --> 00:07:59.390
Lastly, don't ignore
the developmental role.

