00:08:34.140 --> 00:08:36.090
Example, one question.

00:08:36.360 --> 00:08:39.959
Which of the following is the primary
objective of the Reserve Bank of

00:08:39.959 --> 00:08:41.789
India as a monetary authority?

00:08:42.179 --> 00:08:44.370
A. Maximizing government revenue.

00:08:44.579 --> 00:08:46.650
B, maintaining price stability.

00:08:46.800 --> 00:08:49.410
C. Promoting foreign trade exclusively.

00:08:49.640 --> 00:08:53.750
D providing loans directly to the
public understand the question

00:08:53.750 --> 00:08:55.280
before moving to explanation.

00:08:55.730 --> 00:08:59.360
The question asks for the main
goal of RBI's, monetary authority

00:08:59.360 --> 00:09:03.200
role, option A. Maximizing
revenue is the government's job.

00:09:03.560 --> 00:09:06.830
Option C is part of its
foreign role, but not primary.

00:09:07.160 --> 00:09:09.080
Option D is what commercial banks.

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:11.440
So B is the correct answer.

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:15.550
Maintaining price stability is the
core objective of its monetary policy.

00:09:16.060 --> 00:09:17.770
Example two question.

00:09:18.040 --> 00:09:21.700
The Reserve Bank of India acts
as the lender of last resort for

00:09:21.700 --> 00:09:23.200
which of the following entities?

00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:25.150
A individual citizens.

00:09:25.330 --> 00:09:28.330
B State governments, C, commercial banks.

00:09:28.330 --> 00:09:30.215
D, international Monetary Fund.

00:09:30.805 --> 00:09:32.155
Understand the question before.

00:09:32.155 --> 00:09:33.325
Moving to explanation.

00:09:33.745 --> 00:09:37.975
The term lender of last resort
means providing emergency liquidity.

00:09:38.305 --> 00:09:40.285
RBI doesn't lend to individuals.

00:09:40.345 --> 00:09:44.515
So A is out, it is a banker to state
governments, but this specific term

00:09:44.515 --> 00:09:46.315
applies to financial institutions.

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:48.710
The IMF is an international body.

00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:53.450
This role is specifically for commercial
banks to prevent a system-wide crisis.

00:09:53.510 --> 00:09:54.830
So C is correct.

00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:59.420
Example three question, which
act primarily governs the Reserve

00:09:59.420 --> 00:10:02.660
Bank of India's functions related
to foreign exchange management.

00:10:02.990 --> 00:10:09.440
A Banking Regulation Act 1949 B.
Reserve Bank of India Act 1934 C.

00:10:09.530 --> 00:10:15.650
Foreign Exchange Management Act, FEMA
1999 D. Negotiable Instruments Act 1891.

00:10:15.925 --> 00:10:18.415
Understand the question
before Moving to explanation.

00:10:18.835 --> 00:10:21.685
The question is about the Law
For Foreign Exchange Management.

00:10:22.045 --> 00:10:26.905
The Banking Regulation Act is for banking
rules, the RBI Act, established RBI.

00:10:27.175 --> 00:10:29.905
The Negotiable Instruments
Act is for things like checks.

00:10:30.235 --> 00:10:34.225
The Foreign Exchange Management
Act of FEMA 1999 was specifically

00:10:34.225 --> 00:10:35.575
created for this purpose.

00:10:35.845 --> 00:10:38.155
RBI is the authority that implements it.

00:10:38.305 --> 00:10:40.135
Therefore, C is the correct answer.

